    "causal_summary": "The Memory MCP fuses ranked signals and renders a result set the downstream agent loop caches against, but its ordering is not reproducible: the candidate-merge comparators sort score-only with non-content tie-breaks (input-order or clock-derived `updatedat`), the four ranked ANN `ORDER BY distance` queries have no tie-break so which rows survive the LIMIT into fusion is run-to-run unstable, and recall serialization is a bare `JSON.stringify` with no content-derived render-order stage (`research.md` Internal Baseline, `001` iter-3 Q5)",
